.TH SDL_HapticPeriodic 3type "SDL 3.1.2" "Simple Directmedia Layer" "SDL3 DATATYPES"
.SH NAME
SDL_HapticPeriodic \- A structure containing a template for a Periodic effect\[char46]
.SH HEADER FILE
Defined in SDL3/SDL_haptic\[char46]h

.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include \(dqSDL3/SDL.h\(dq
.PP
.BI "typedef struct SDL_HapticPeriodic
.BI "{
.BI "    /* Header */
.BI "    Uint16 type;        /**< SDL_HAPTIC_SINE, SDL_HAPTIC_SQUARE
.BI "                             SDL_HAPTIC_TRIANGLE, SDL_HAPTIC_SAWTOOTHUP or
.BI "                             SDL_HAPTIC_SAWTOOTHDOWN */
.BI "    SDL_HapticDirection direction;  /**< Direction of the effect. */
.BI "
.BI "    /* Replay */
.BI "    Uint32 length;      /**< Duration of the effect. */
.BI "    Uint16 delay;       /**< Delay before starting the effect. */
.BI "
.BI "    /* Trigger */
.BI "    Uint16 button;      /**< Button that triggers the effect. */
.BI "    Uint16 interval;    /**< How soon it can be triggered again after button. */
.BI "
.BI "    /* Periodic */
.BI "    Uint16 period;      /**< Period of the wave. */
.BI "    Sint16 magnitude;   /**< Peak value; if negative, equivalent to 180 degrees extra phase shift. */
.BI "    Sint16 offset;      /**< Mean value of the wave. */
.BI "    Uint16 phase;       /**< Positive phase shift given by hundredth of a degree. */
.BI "
.BI "    /* Envelope */
.BI "    Uint16 attack_length;   /**< Duration of the attack. */
.BI "    Uint16 attack_level;    /**< Level at the start of the attack. */
.BI "    Uint16 fade_length; /**< Duration of the fade. */
.BI "    Uint16 fade_level;  /**< Level at the end of the fade. */
.BI "} SDL_HapticPeriodic;
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The struct handles the following effects:


\(bu 
.BR SDL_HAPTIC_SINE


\(bu 
.BR SDL_HAPTIC_SQUARE


\(bu 
.BR SDL_HAPTIC_TRIANGLE


\(bu 
.BR SDL_HAPTIC_SAWTOOTHUP


\(bu 
.BR SDL_HAPTIC_SAWTOOTHDOWN


A periodic effect consists in a wave-shaped effect that repeats itself over
time\[char46] The type determines the shape of the wave and the parameters
determine the dimensions of the wave\[char46]

Phase is given by hundredth of a degree meaning that giving the phase a
value of 9000 will displace it 25% of its period\[char46] Here are sample values:


\(bu 0: No phase displacement\[char46]

\(bu 9000: Displaced 25% of its period\[char46]

\(bu 18000: Displaced 50% of its period\[char46]

\(bu 27000: Displaced 75% of its period\[char46]

\(bu 36000: Displaced 100% of its period, same as 0, but 0 is preferred\[char46]

Examples:
.BR 

.BR 
  SDL_HAPTIC_SINE
    __      __      __      __
   /  \    /  \    /  \    /
  /    \__/    \__/    \__/

  SDL_HAPTIC_SQUARE
   __    __    __    __    __
  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |
  |  |__|  |__|  |__|  |__|  |

  SDL_HAPTIC_TRIANGLE
    /\    /\    /\    /\    /\
   /  \  /  \  /  \  /  \  /
  /    \/    \/    \/    \/

  SDL_HAPTIC_SAWTOOTHUP
    /|  /|  /|  /|  /|  /|  /|
   / | / | / | / | / | / | / |
  /  |/  |/  |/  |/  |/  |/  |

  SDL_HAPTIC_SAWTOOTHDOWN
  \  |\  |\  |\  |\  |\  |\  |
   \ | \ | \ | \ | \ | \ | \ |
    \|  \|  \|  \|  \|  \|  \|


.BR 

